column3: “Sweet Jane is rather good. Doesn't have these couch locking symptoms. Really vivid head high accompanied by some visuals if you smoke a lot. Does make me really sleepy at the end of the trip, indica like. Also gave me a little headache throughout. Munchies were real. 7/10 not good not bad.”
“Inspirational! Thanks to this sweet gal I was gleefully awake till 4 am creating a Minotaur costume.”
“it’s okay not really something i’d but again. not really a motivational strain, yes focused & clear head head. but does give a slight head ache.”
“there is no refrence to the song Sweet Jane" by The Velvet Underground other than that its worth trying of course”"

“Used the 1:1 tincture and it definitely provides an overall relaxation and steady calmness. Using it for cancer pain and mental anxiety/stress. I'm prone to even more paranoia under the influence of marijuana. 

I noticed after I ran out, I was anxious for it, not realizing how much it truly helps me relax overall. I didn't get a euphoric spacey or happy high, or paranoia, it provides a steady heavy relaxed high. Def...”
“special flawor,  really good taste,  you Can smell it all night Long because of that rosy sweetie kinda citrus flavor ..damn nice , Also really good high , really Light happy high”
“This strain sounds beautiful haha, I'll re do comment if I get to try this one day 😊”

“A rose is as sweet when you name it after marijuana.
I like the sweet jane strain. Flowery fruit is its enjoyable fragrance.
Satisfyingly a one hit wonder that is able to give a feeling of dancing on the ceiling. 
OH BOY That is My GIRL getting me high!
 I love a good sativa and this is a great sativa.
The ladies working at Serra dispensary where I found this strain were just as beautiful as the Sweet Jane flower its...”
